#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.42"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.42:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.42:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga "
msgstr "4. Deities "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 42. Paṭhamaniddasasutta → paṭhamaniddesavatthusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.42:0.3"
msgid "42. Paṭhamaniddasasutta "
msgstr "42. Graduation (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.35, sc1
msgctxt "an7.42:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Sāriputta robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "an7.42:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to him, "

msgctxt "an7.42:1.3"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ. "
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "an7.42:1.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.42:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and exchanged greetings with the wanderers there. "

msgctxt "an7.42:1.6"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.42:1.7"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time while those wanderers who follow other paths were sitting together this discussion came up among them, "

msgctxt "an7.42:1.8"
msgid "“yo hi koci, āvuso, dvādasavassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, ‘niddaso bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, anyone who lives the full and pure spiritual life for twelve years is qualified to be called a ‘graduate mendicant’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.42:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandi nappaṭikkosi. "
msgstr "Sāriputta neither approved nor dismissed that statement of the wanderers who follow other paths. "

msgctxt "an7.42:2.2"
msgid "Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi: "
msgstr "He got up from his seat, thinking, "

msgctxt "an7.42:2.3"
msgid "“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.42:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened, adding: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.36, sc3
msgctxt "an7.42:3.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.2"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.3"
msgid "‘atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.6"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.7"
msgid "Tena kho pana, bhante, samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.8"
msgid "‘yo hi koci, āvuso, dvādasavassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, niddaso bhikkhūti alaṃvacanāyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.9"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandiṃ nappaṭikkosiṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: pakkamiṃ → pakkāmiṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.42:3.10"
msgid "Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.11"
msgid "‘bhagavato santike etassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.42:3.12"
msgid "Sakkā nu kho, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye kevalaṃ vassagaṇanamattena niddaso bhikkhu paññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, in this teaching and training can we describe a mendicant as a ‘graduate’ solely because they have completed a certain number of years?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.42:4.1"
msgid "“Na kho, sāriputta, sakkā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye kevalaṃ vassagaṇanamattena niddaso bhikkhu paññāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "“No, Sāriputta, we cannot. "

msgctxt "an7.42:4.2"
msgid "Satta kho imāni, sāriputta, niddasavatthūni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "I make known these seven qualifications for graduation after realizing them with my own insight. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.37, sc5
msgctxt "an7.42:5.1"
msgid "Katamāni satta? "
msgstr "What seven? "

msgctxt "an7.42:5.2"
msgid "Idha, sāriputta, bhikkhu sikkhāsamādāne tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca sikkhāsamādāne avigatapemo, dhammanisantiyā tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca dhammanisantiyā avigatapemo, icchāvinaye tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca icchāvinaye avigatapemo, paṭisallāne tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca paṭisallāne avigatapemo, vīriyārambhe tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca vīriyārambhe avigatapemo, satinepakke tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca satinepakke avigatapemo, diṭṭhipaṭivedhe tibbacchando hoti āyatiñca diṭṭhipaṭivedhe avigatapemo. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has a keen enthusiasm to undertake the training … to examine the teachings … to get rid of desires … for retreat … to rouse up energy … for mindfulness and alertness … to penetrate theoretically. And they don’t lose these desires in the future. "

msgctxt "an7.42:5.3"
msgid "Imāni kho, sāriputta, satta niddasavatthūni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "These are the seven qualifications for graduation that I make known after realizing them with my own insight. "

msgctxt "an7.42:5.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, sāriputta, sattahi niddasavatthūhi samannāgato bhikkhu dvādasa cepi vassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, ‘niddaso bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya; "
msgstr "A mendicant who has these seven qualifications for graduation is qualified to be called a ‘graduate mendicant’. This is so whether they have lived the full and pure spiritual life for twelve years, "

msgctxt "an7.42:5.5"
msgid "catubbīsati cepi vassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, ‘niddaso bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya; "
msgstr "twenty-four years, "

msgctxt "an7.42:5.6"
msgid "chattiṃsati cepi vassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, ‘niddaso bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya, aṭṭhacattārīsañcepi vassāni paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carati, ‘niddaso bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "thirty-six years, or forty-eight years.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.42:5.7"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

